# Railway Production Environment Configuration Example
# This file shows the format Railway will use for environment variables
# Copy this content to Railway's environment variables section

# ===================================
# SERVER CONFIGURATION
# ===================================
PORT=8080
HOST=0.0.0.0
ENV=production

# ===================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION (Railway MySQL)
# ===================================
# Railway automatically provides these when you add MySQL service:
# DB_HOST=${{MySQL.MYSQL_HOST}}
# DB_PORT=${{MySQL.MYSQL_PORT}}
# DB_USER=${{MySQL.MYSQL_USER}}
# DB_PASSWORD=${{MySQL.MYSQL_PASSWORD}}
# DB_NAME=${{MySQL.MYSQL_DATABASE}}
# DATABASE_URL=${{MySQL.DATABASE_URL}}

# Example values (Railway will generate real ones):
# DB_HOST=containers-us-west-xx.railway.app
# DB_PORT=3306
# DB_USER=root
# DB_PASSWORD=your-railway-generated-password
# DB_NAME=railway
# DATABASE_URL=mysql://root:password@host:3306/railway

# ===================================
# SECURITY CONFIGURATION
# ===================================
# IMPORTANT: Set this to a secure secret in Railway dashboard
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secure-jwt-secret-for-production-change-this-immediately

# ===================================
# CORS CONFIGURATION
# ===================================
# Add your frontend domain(s) - update these with your actual domains
CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend.railway.app,https://your-custom-domain.com

# ===================================
# OPTIONAL: REDIS CONFIGURATION
# ===================================
# If you add Redis service to Railway, these will be auto-generated:
# REDIS_URL=${{Redis.REDIS_URL}}
# REDIS_PORT=${{Redis.REDIS_PORT}}

# ===================================
# RAILWAY DEPLOYMENT STEPS
# ===================================
# 1. Go to https://railway.app and create account
# 2. Create new project
# 3. Add MySQL service (Railway will auto-generate DB variables)
# 4. Add your Go app from GitHub repository
# 5. Set these environment variables manually in Railway dashboard:
#    - JWT_SECRET (secure random string)
#    - CORS_ORIGINS (your frontend URL)
# 6. Railway will automatically set all ${{MySQL.*}} variables
# 7. Deploy and test endpoints

# ===================================
# TESTING AFTER DEPLOYMENT
# ===================================
# Test these URLs after deployment:
# https://your-app.railway.app/health
# https://your-app.railway.app/api/v1/stocks
# https://your-app.railway.app/api/v1/ws/status
# https://your-app.railway.app/ (root endpoint)

# ===================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ===================================
# If connection fails:
# 1. Check Railway MySQL service is running
# 2. Verify environment variables are set correctly
# 3. Check Railway logs for connection errors
# 4. Ensure TLS/SSL is properly configured (handled automatically by our config)
# 5. Test database connection manually using Railway CLI:
#    railway connect MySQL 